	<div class="wrapper">
		<div class="intro-alt intro--event-detailed intro--event-detailed-bg">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="intro__head"></div><!-- /.intro__head -->
			</div><!-- /.container -->
		</div><!-- /.intro-alt -->
		<div class="section-ordinary decoration-dark-gradient">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section__body">
					<div class="event-detailed">
						<div class="row align-items-center">
							<div class="col-lg-5">
								<div class="event__image">
                  <% if @event.tour.artist.images.present? &&  @event.tour.artist.default_image.image_url.present? %>
                    <img src="<%= @event.tour.artist.default_image.image_url %>">
                  <% else %>
                    <%= image_tag("client/temp/event-detailed.jpg", alt: "") %>
                  <% end %>
								</div><!-- /.event__image -->
							</div><!-- /.col-lg-5 -->
							<div class="col-lg-7">
								<div class="event__body">
									<div class="event__head">
										<h1>
											<%= @event.tour.artist.name.humanize %>
										</h1>
										
										<h2>
											<%= @event.name %>
										</h2>
										
										<p>
											<%= @event.tour.tour_subtitle %>
										</p>
									</div><!-- /.event__head -->

									<div class="event__location">
										<p>
											<%= event_detail_address(@event.tour) %>
										</p>
										<p>
											<%= event_day_name(@event) %>
										</p>
									</div><!-- /.event__location -->

									<div class="event__time">
										<p class="red">
          									<%= t("client.events.show.p1") %>
											 <%= event_door_time(@event) %> / Show: <%= event_show_time(@event.show_time) %>
										</p><!-- /.red -->

										<p>
											<span>
          										<%= t("client.events.show.p6") %>
												
											</span>
										</p>
									</div><!-- /.event__time -->

									<div class="event__price">
										<p>
											<%= @event.ticket_price %>0$
										</p>
									</div><!-- /.event__price -->

									<div class="event__actions">
										<a href="#" class="btn btn--small" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#exampleModal">
          									<%= t("client.events.show.p5") %>
										</a>

										<a href="#" class="btn btn--small">
          									<%= t("client.events.show.p4") %>
										</a>
									<div class="event__like event_liked_unliked" style="z-index: 5;cursor: pointer;padding-left: 10px;" data-liked="<%= current_user.liked?(@event) %>" data-event-id="<%= @event.id %>" id="event_liked_unliked<%= @event.id %>">
										<% if current_user.liked?(@event) %>
										    <img src="<%= image_url 'client/svg/heart-2.svg'%>" id="like-img-<%= @event.id %>" width="32" alt="">
										<% else %>
										  <img src="<%= image_url 'client/svg/heart.svg'%>" id="like-img-<%= @event.id %>"  width="32" alt="">
										<% end %>
									</div><!-- /.event__like -->
									</div><!-- /.event__actions -->
								</div><!-- /.event__body -->
							</div><!-- /.col-lg-7 -->
						</div><!-- /.row -->

						<div class="event__additional">
							<a href="<%= albums_artist_path @event.tour.artist.id %>" class="btn btn--small ajaxLink">
								
								<%= t("client.events.show.p3") %>

							</a>

							<a href="#">
								<i class="icon-play"></i>
							</a>
							
							<a href="#">
								<i class="icon-two-arrows"></i>
							</a>
							
							<a href="#">
								<i class="icon-plus"></i>
							</a>
						</div><!-- /.event__additional -->
					</div><!-- /.event-detailed -->
				</div><!-- /.section__body -->
			</div><!-- /.container -->
		</div><!-- /.section-ordinary decoration-dark-gradient -->

		<section class="section-ordinary section-about  pb-5 mb-5">
			<div class="container">
				<header class="section__head">
					<h3>
						<%= t("client.events.show.p2") %>

					</h3>
				</header><!-- /.section__head -->

				<div class="section__body">
					<p>
            But I must explain to you how all this mistaken idea of denouncing pleasure and praising pain was born and I will give you a complete account of the system, and expound the actual
            teachings of the great explorer of the truth, the master-builder of human happiness. No one rejects, dislikes, or avoids pleasure itself, because it is pleasure, but because
            those who do not know how to pursue pleasure rationally encounter consequences that are extremely painful. Nor again is there anyone who loves or pursues or desires to obtain
            pain of itself, because it is pain, but because occasionally circumstances occur in which toil and pain can procure him some great pleasure. To take a trivial example, which
            of us ever undertakes laborious physical exercise, except to obtain some advantage from it? But who has any right to find fault with a man who chooses to enjoy a pleasure
            that has no annoying consequences, or one who avoids a pain that produces no resultant pleasure?" "On the other hand, we denounce with righteous indignation and dislike men
            who are so beguiled and demoralized by the charms of pleasure of the moment, so blinded by desire, that they cannot foresee the pain and trouble that are bound to ensue; and
            equal blame belongs to those who fail in their duty through weakness of will, which is the same as saying through shrinking from toil and pain. These cases are perfectly simple
            and easy to distinguish. In a free hour, when our power of choice is untrammelled and when nothing prevents our being able To Do what we like best, every pleasure is to be
            welcomed and every pain avoided. But in certain circumstances and owing to the claims of duty or the obligations of business it will frequently occur that pleasures have to
            be repudiated and annoyances accepted. The wise man therefore always holds in these matters to this principle of selection: he rejects pleasures to secure other greater pleasures,
            or else he endures pains to avoid worse pain.
					</p>
				</div><!-- /.section__body -->
			</div><!-- /.container -->
		</section><!-- /.section-ordinary -->
    <%= render partial: 'client/events/tour_dates', locals: { tour_dates: @tour_dates } %>
		
	</div><!-- /.wrapper -->


